-- QATAR
('any', 'qatar', 'Work', 'Qatar Work Visa (Residence Permit)',
 'Qatar is a major employer destination in the Middle East, especially for construction, healthcare, education, and finance. The employer sponsors the work visa and residence permit. Qatar reformed its kafala system in 2021, allowing workers to change jobs more freely.',
 'Must have a job offer from a Qatar-registered employer who initiates the visa process. No personal work visa applications — all processing is employer-led. Medical examination required upon arrival. Must be under 60 years old for most work categories.',
 'Job offer/contract from Qatari employer, valid passport (6+ months validity), educational certificates (attested), medical fitness certificate, passport photos.',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks (employer process)', 'QAR 200–500 (employer pays)',
 'work', '2–4 weeks', '2 years, renewable', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'qatar', 'Study', 'Student Visa (Qatar)',
 'Qatar is home to Education City, which hosts campuses of prestigious international universities including Cornell, Georgetown, Northwestern, and others. Students obtain residence permits through their educational institution.',
 'Must be enrolled at a Qatar-accredited institution. Education City institutions manage most of the visa process. Must pass medical examination.',
 'Enrollment letter, valid passport, passport photos, medical examination, financial means proof.',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks', 'QAR 100–300',
 'study', '2–4 weeks', 'Duration of studies', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'qatar', 'Digital Nomad', 'Tourist Visa / Short-Stay',
 '⚠️ Qatar does not have a digital nomad visa. Citizens of 95 countries can visit Qatar visa-free for up to 30–90 days. Qatar is primarily a transit and business destination. Working remotely for foreign companies while on a tourist visa is in a legal grey area.',
 'Visa-free entry for 95+ nationalities for 30–90 days. Must have return ticket, sufficient funds, and accommodation plans. Working for Qatari companies requires a separate work permit.',
 'Valid passport, return ticket, accommodation, sufficient funds.',
 'Visa-free: immediate', 'Free (visa-free countries) or QAR 100–200 (visa required countries)',
 'digital_nomad', 'Immediate (visa-free)', '30–90 days (visa-free)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'qatar', 'Retirement', 'Long-Term Residence (Permanent Residency for Expatriates)',
 'Qatar introduced a permanent residency card scheme in 2018 for select expats who have lived in Qatar for 20+ years or have special achievements. Additionally, a long-term "privileged residency" was introduced in 2020 for investors and special categories.',
 'Standard permanent residency: 20+ years of legal continuous residence in Qatar. Privileged Residency (2020): Investors of at least QAR 5,000,000 in Qatar real estate, or spouses/children of Qatari citizens, or those with outstanding achievements.',
 'Proof of continuous residence (20+ years), or investment documentation (QAR 5,000,000), or relevant achievement documentation. Valid passport, health insurance.',
 'Typically 6–12 months for privileged residency application', 'QAR 1,000–5,000',
 'retirement', '6–12 months', 'Permanent (renewable annually)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'qatar', 'Investor', 'Qatar Privileged Residency (Investor)',
 'Qatar''s Privileged Residency scheme (2020) grants long-term/permanent residency to investors in real estate or business. Two tracks: QAR 5,000,000 in Qatari real estate with full ownership (can also use QAR 3,750,000 in QIFF-regulated funds), or qualifying business investment.',
 'Investment Track A: Minimum QAR 5,000,000 in Qatari real estate or QAR 3,750,000 in regulated investment funds. Investment Track B: Business investment with approval from Ministry of Commerce. No age restriction.',
 'Investment documentation (property title deed or fund investment certificate), proof of funds and legitimate source, valid passport, medical examination.',
 'Typically 3–6 months', 'QAR 1,000–5,000',
 'investor', '3–6 months', 'Permanent (annually renewable)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'qatar', 'Family', 'Family Sponsorship (Qatar)',
 'Qatar residents with a valid Residence Permit (RP) who earn above the minimum sponsorship income can sponsor their spouse and children to join them. The minimum salary for family sponsorship varies by family size.',
 'Must hold a valid Qatar Residence Permit. Must earn at least QAR 10,000/month (approximately USD 2,750) to sponsor spouse; higher for larger families. Housing must be appropriate for family size.',
 'Sponsor''s Residence Permit, marriage certificate (attested by Qatar embassy or apostilled), birth certificates for children, sponsor''s payslips and rental contract, valid passports for family members.',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks', 'QAR 200–500 per person',
 'family', '2–4 weeks', 'Tied to sponsor''s RP (typically 1–3 years)', CURRENT_DATE),

-- SAUDI ARABIA
('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Work', 'Saudi Work Visa + Iqama (Residence Permit)',
 'Saudi Arabia is one of the world''s largest labor markets for expatriates. Employers (sponsors/kafeel) initiate the work visa process. The Iqama (residence permit) is obtained after arrival. Saudi Arabia has been liberalizing its labor market under Vision 2030 reforms.',
 'Must have a job offer from a Saudi-registered employer who serves as the visa sponsor (kafeel). Must pass medical examination. Work visa types vary: work and residence visa (single/multiple entry). Must be under 60 years old for most categories.',
 'Employment contract (attested by Saudi Embassy), valid passport (6+ months), passport photos, medical fitness certificate (including HIV test), educational credentials (attested), criminal background check.',
 'Typically 2–6 weeks (employer process)', 'SAR 200–2,000 (employer pays most fees)',
 'work', '2–6 weeks', 'Iqama: 1–2 years, renewable', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Study', 'Saudi Student Visa',
 'International students studying at Saudi universities (including world-ranked King Abdullah University of Science and Technology — KAUST which is tuition-free) can obtain student visas. Saudi Arabia offers generous government scholarships for foreign students.',
 'Must be enrolled at a Saudi Ministry of Education-accredited institution. KAUST: open international applications, tuition-free with stipend. Other universities: acceptance letter required. Must pass medical examination.',
 'Enrollment/acceptance letter, valid passport, medical fitness certificate, passport photos, financial means proof (if not on scholarship).',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks', 'SAR 100–500',
 'study', '2–4 weeks', 'Duration of studies, renewable', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Digital Nomad', 'Saudi Tourist e-Visa / Visit Visa',
 '⚠️ Saudi Arabia does not have a digital nomad visa. In 2019, Saudi Arabia opened tourism for the first time, offering e-visas to 49 nationalities. Remote workers visiting Saudi Arabia typically use the tourist e-visa. Working for Saudi companies requires a separate work permit.',
 'E-visa: citizens of 49 eligible countries. Must have return ticket, accommodation, sufficient funds. Working remotely for non-Saudi companies while on a tourist visa is in a legal grey area.',
 'Valid passport, e-visa application (online), return ticket, accommodation proof.',
 'E-visa: typically 3–5 days', 'SAR 440 (tourist e-visa)',
 'digital_nomad', '3–5 days (e-visa)', 'E-visa: 90 days per visit, valid for 1 year multiple-entry', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Retirement', 'Saudi Premium Residency (Platinum Residency)',
 'Saudi Arabia''s Premium Residency program (launched 2019, expanded 2021) grants long-term or permanent residency to qualifying investors and individuals. Platinum Residency: SAR 800,000 one-time fee for permanent status. Annual Premium Residency: SAR 100,000/year.',
 'Platinum Residency: one-time payment of SAR 800,000 (approximately USD 213,000) for permanent residency. Annual Premium: SAR 100,000/year (approximately USD 26,700). Must have no criminal record. No age or minimum income requirement.',
 'Payment of fee, valid passport, medical examination, criminal background check.',
 'Typically 1–3 months', 'SAR 100,000/year or SAR 800,000 (one-time permanent)',
 'retirement', '1–3 months', 'Annual renewal or Permanent (Platinum)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Investor', 'Saudi Investment Visa / Special Integrated Logistics Zone Permits',
 'Saudi Arabia is actively attracting foreign investment under Vision 2030. The Saudi Investment Authority (SAGIA/MISA) issues investment licenses. Special Economic Zones (Neom, King Abdullah Economic City, etc.) have specific investor incentives including residency rights.',
 'Must establish or invest in a Saudi business registered with MISA (Ministry of Investment). 100% foreign ownership is now allowed in most sectors. Minimum investment varies by sector and zone.',
 'MISA investment license, company registration documents, proof of investment capital, valid passport, medical examination.',
 'Typically 2–4 months (MISA process)', 'SAR 2,000–10,000 (MISA fees)',
 'investor', '2–4 months', 'Iqama: 1–2 years renewable; Premium Residency option after 1 year', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'saudi-arabia', 'Family', 'Family Iqama (Dependent Residency)',
 'Saudi Iqama holders earning above the income threshold can sponsor their spouse and children as dependents. Dependent family members must also pass medical examinations. Different rules apply for domestic workers.',
 'Must hold a valid Saudi Iqama. Must earn at least SAR 4,000/month to sponsor spouse only; SAR 6,000/month for spouse + children. Housing must be appropriate.',
 'Sponsor''s Iqama, marriage certificate (attested by Saudi Embassy), birth certificates for children, sponsor''s payslips, medical fitness certificates for family members.',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks', 'SAR 400–800 per person',
 'family', '2–4 weeks', 'Tied to sponsor''s Iqama', CURRENT_DATE),

-- ISRAEL
('any', 'israel', 'Work', 'B-1 Work Visa / Expert Visa',
 'Israel''s B-1 work visa is for foreign nationals employed by Israeli companies. Israel''s thriving tech ecosystem ("Startup Nation") attracts significant skilled talent. The Expert Visa is a common route for specialized professionals in tech, engineering, and medicine.',
 'Must have a job offer from an Israeli employer. Expert visa: requires specialized skills not readily available in the Israeli labor market. General B-1: employer sponsors through the Ministry of Interior. Salary must meet minimum threshold.',
 'Employment contract, valid passport, employer''s company registration, educational qualifications, criminal background check.',
 'Typically 2–4 months (including employer sponsorship process)', 'USD 100–300',
 'work', '2–4 months', '1 year, renewable (up to 5 years maximum)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'israel', 'Study', 'Student Visa (A-2)',
 'International students enrolled at Israeli universities can obtain a student visa (A-2) and subsequent residence permit (A-1 after 6 months). Israel has world-ranked universities including Weizmann Institute, Hebrew University, and Technion.',
 'Must be enrolled at an Israeli Ministry of Education-accredited institution. Must demonstrate financial means (approximately USD 1,000/month). Must have health insurance.',
 'Enrollment letter from Israeli institution, financial proof, health insurance, valid passport, criminal background check.',
 'Typically 2–4 weeks (at Israeli embassy)', 'USD 100–200',
 'study', '2–4 weeks', '1 year, renewable', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'israel', 'Digital Nomad', 'Tourist Visa (B-2) – Remote Work',
 'Israel does not have a dedicated digital nomad visa. Most nationalities can enter Israel visa-free for 90 days. Remote workers continuing work for foreign employers while on a tourist visa are generally tolerated but not explicitly authorized. Tel Aviv is a popular tech hub.',
 'Citizens of 100+ countries can enter Israel visa-free for 90 days. Must have return ticket, accommodation, sufficient funds. Must not be conducting work for Israeli companies without a work visa.',
 'Valid passport, return ticket, sufficient funds, accommodation details.',
 'Visa-free: immediate at airport', 'Free (visa-free countries)',
 'digital_nomad', 'Immediate (visa-free)', 'Up to 90 days (extendable to 6 months in some cases)', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'israel', 'Retirement', 'Aliyah (Jewish Immigration) / Long-Term Residency',
 'The primary long-term immigration pathway to Israel is Aliyah — immigration for Jewish people under the Law of Return, granting immediate citizenship. Non-Jewish retirees have limited options: repeated tourist stays (90 days max per entry for most nationalities), or marriage to an Israeli citizen.',
 'Aliyah: Must be Jewish (by birth — Jewish mother or grandmother — or by halachic conversion) or spouse/child/grandchild of a Jewish person. Non-Jewish options: marriage to Israeli citizen, or outstanding professional status (B-1 expert).',
 'Aliyah: proof of Jewish identity (Jewish community membership, rabbinical letter, birth certificates showing Jewish lineage), valid passport. Non-Jewish: proof of qualifying relationship to Israeli citizen.',
 'Aliyah: typically 3–6 months (through Jewish Agency); Non-Jewish: varies', 'Aliyah: minimal fees (Jewish Agency assistance available)',
 'retirement', '3–6 months (Aliyah)', 'Aliyah: permanent citizenship; Non-Jewish: limited options', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'israel', 'Investor', 'Investor Visa / Innovation Authority Programs',
 'Israel actively attracts foreign investors, especially in tech, biotech, and cleantech through the Israel Innovation Authority (IIA) programs. Foreign companies establishing R&D centers in Israel can receive significant grants. The B-1 Expert Visa covers investors managing their Israeli businesses.',
 'Must establish a business or make a qualifying investment in Israel. IIA programs require meeting specific tech/innovation criteria. No minimum investment amount for general business visa, but investment must be substantial and create economic benefit.',
 'Company registration documents (registered in Israel), investment proof, valid passport, business plan.',
 'Typically 2–4 months', 'USD 100–500',
 'investor', '2–4 months', '1 year, renewable', CURRENT_DATE),

('any', 'israel', 'Family', 'Family Reunification Visa / Citizenship under Law of Return',
 'Spouses of Israeli citizens can obtain an A-5 residence permit and eventually citizenship. Under the Law of Return, spouses, children, and grandchildren of Jews may also be eligible for Aliyah.',
 'A-5 for spouse of Israeli citizen: must be legally married to an Israeli citizen, genuine relationship. Law of Return: spouse/child/grandchild of a Jewish person. Same-sex partnerships recognized for immigration purposes (but not marriage by Israeli law).',
 'Marriage certificate, Israeli citizen''s documents, proof of genuine relationship (for A-5), valid passport.',
 'A-5: typically 3–6 months; Aliyah: 3–6 months', 'USD 100–300',
 'family', '3–6 months', 'A-5: gradual — temporary, then permanent after 4+ years; Aliyah: immediate citizenship', CURRENT_DATE),

