('any', 'morocco', 'Retirement', 'Residence Card for Financially Independent Persons',
 'Morocco is a popular retirement destination for Europeans and North Americans, especially in Marrakech, Essaouira, and Tangier. Long-term retirees can obtain a Carte de Séjour (residence card) as financially independent persons.',
 'Must demonstrate passive income sufficient to cover living costs in Morocco without working. Typically: EUR 2,000–3,000/month from pension or investments. Must have health insurance. No minimum age requirement.',
